 
GENDER PAY GAP REPORT 

 

GreenZone  Cleaning  &  Support  Services  is  required  by  law  to  publish  an  annual  gender  pay  gap 
report. This is its report for the snapshot date of 5 April 2017. 

We are committed to the principle of equal opportunities and equal treatment for all employees, 
regardless of  sex,  race,  religion or belief,  age,  marriage  or  civil  partnership,  pregnancy/maternity, 
sexual orientation, gender reassignment or disability. We  have a  clear policy of paying employees 
equally for the same or equivalent work, regardless of their sex (or any other characteristic set out 
above).   

We are confident that our gender pay gap does not stem from paying men and women differently 
for the same or equivalent work. Rather its gender pay gap is the result of the roles in which men 
and women work within the organisation and the salaries that these roles attract.  

The  figures  set  out  below  have  been  calculated  using  the  standard  methodologies  used  in  the 
Equality Act 2010 (Gender Pay Gap Information) Regulations 2017.  

 

Summary 

  The mean Gender Pay Gap is 3.1% 
  The median Gender Pay Gap is 2.6 % 
  The mean bonus Gender Pay Gap is 11.1 % 
  The median bonus Gender Pay Gap is 0% 
  The proportion of males receiving a bonus payment is 6.5% 
  The proportion of females receiving a bonus payment is 5% 
 
  Proportion of males and females in each quartile  

 
