3.1 % 
2.6 % 

On average female employees earned 3.1% less than men overall including Head Office staff.  The 
difference  is  even  lower  when  we  look  at  the  numbers  for  our  core  business  group  –  cleaning 
operatives where the mean average of 1.8% and the median is 0%.  

This is a positive result considering that the national UK Gender Pay Gap currently stands at 9.1 %.   

 

2.  Bonus Pay Gap 

 
Mean 
Median 
 

Difference 
11.1% 
0.0% 

Whilst the Mean Bonus Pay Gap shows a difference of 11.1% between male and female employees, 
the Median Bonus Pay Gap shows a 0.0%.  

Across the UK economy as a whole, men are more likely than women to be in senior roles (especially 
very senior roles at the top of organisations), and this is also the case in our organisation as reflected 
on our mean bonus pay gap (11.1%). However,  the median bonus pay gap (0.0%) shows that overall 
across  the  company,  bonuses  are  balanced  and  reflect  no  difference  between  male  and  female 
employees. 

 

 

 

 

